<section class="section exposing-a-myth" id="exposing-a-myth" aria-labelledby="exposing-a-myth-title">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__head">
      <h2 id="exposing-a-myth-title">BIBLE PRESENTATIONS NEAR YOU:</h2>
      <p>
        Using only the Bible, these regionally delivered talks will provide convincing evidence of
        where temptation and sin come from.
        They will debunk the idea of a fallen angel, a supernatural being that God permits to torment men and women.
        The talks will demonstrate where the concept Satan originated, and why you should not live in fear.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="exposing-a-myth__card-wrap">
      <article class="exposing-a-myth__card" aria-labelledby="exposing-card-title">
        <header class="exposing-a-myth__card-banner">
          <h3 id="exposing-card-title" class="exposing-a-myth__card-title">Principles we'll cover:</h3>
          <p class="exposing-a-myth__card-sub"></p>
        </header>

        <ol class="exposing-a-myth__topics">
          <li class="exposing-a-myth__topic">
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-label">Principle 1</span>
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-head">Temptation and sin come from within our hearts, not from external sources.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="exposing-a-myth__topic">
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-label">Principle 2</span>
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-head">There are numerous symbols for sin. None of them are supernatural.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="exposing-a-myth__topic">
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-label">Principle 3</span>
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-head">Satan is often the role of an adversary, accuser, or obstacle. This is why
            Jesus called Peter a “Satan.”</span>
          </li>
          <li class="exposing-a-myth__topic">
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-label">Principle 4</span>
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-head">It is impossible for immortal beings, such as angels, to sin, or eventually be
            destroyed. Immortality cannot be lost.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="exposing-a-myth__topic">
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-label">Principle 5</span>
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-head">Jesus destroyed in himself the power of the devil. He did this by conquering
            temptation and sin.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="exposing-a-myth__topic">
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-label">Principle 6</span>
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-head">There is a world of evil, but it is ruled over by people, not supernatural
            beings.</span>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
